重大决策：
The People's Congress is the highest legislative body.
人们代表大会是最高立法机关
Our country is a democracy.
我们的国家是民主的国家
This is a time for democrats
现在是民主主义者的时代

We are in a democratic society.
我们生活在一个民主社会。
he submitd the report to the commission
他向委员会提交了报告
Another striking feature of the report is the foresight of the development of science and technology .
报告的另一个显著特点是对科技发展的远见。
The Commission meets once every month to set policy.
委员会每月开会一次，制定政策。
The delegates come together to make decision for the group they represent.
代表们聚集在一起，为他们所代表的群体做出决定。
A new initiative is about to be unveiled.
新计划即将出台。
They will be entrusted to solve major national problems.
他们将受托解决国家重大问题。
In order to save money, the state tries to keep non-essential spending to a minimum, always making the most economical decisions.
为了省钱，国家尽量把非必要的开支控制在最低水平，总是做出最经济的决定。
They have a deep knowledge of economic to understand changes in the global market.
他们对经济有很深的了解，能够理解全球市场的变化。
They should not discard the present system entirely. 
他们不应当完全摒弃现行制度。
The plan's implementation is dependent on economic circumstances.
该计划的执行取决于经济情况。
In the past, we were under imperialist oppression, and forced to sign unequal treaties.
过去，我们处于帝国主义压迫之下，被迫签署不平等条约。
They make an evaluation of the plan from a number of perspectives.
他们从多个角度对该计划进行了评估。
They analyzed the advantages and disadvantages of it.
他们分析了它的利弊。
Hitherto, there are no clear answers , but two distinct schools of thought.
到目前为止，还没有明确的答案，但有两种不同的思想流派。
Someone has a conservative attitude.
有人持保守态度。
They prolonged the meeting in order to discuss the point.
他们延长了会期以讨论这个问题。
A congress is held to discuss many controversial issues for many consecutive days and reached a consensus.
连续多日召开代表大会讨论很多有争议的问题，并达成共识。

